            <creation>This story, with the short title "Mary Brings Forth a Spring," is recent: the earliest PEMM manuscript* in which this story appears is from around<date>1879</date>.Originally composed in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName></creation>
            <abstract>
                <p>On the twentieth of Hedar (around November 25), construction began on a new church, but the water in that place soon dried up. They sought water at a nearby spring, but that too had dried up, and they lacked a horse to carry water from a more distant river. When the clergy were on the verge of stopping construction, Mary intervened by establishing a new spring, just as her infant son had done in Egypt. The people collected the water while praising God and thanking Mary.</p>
            </abstract>
